<subSubSection id="C3466526FF86FFC1639BFD25FB1572FE" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE336ADFF86FFC1639BFD25FB1572FE" blockId="8.[151,1437,691,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC1639BFD25FEF975F1" bold="true" box="[151,297,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Description.</emphasis>
Body granulate, small size, slender and macropronotal (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC160AFFD25FBF975F2" box="[931,1065,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Figs. 6A, B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC16732FD25FB5775F1" bold="true" box="[1086,1159,691,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Head:</emphasis>
frontal costa bifurcation located near to the top of vertex; scutellum narrow, with carinae almost parallel; lower margin of the antennal grooves located between of the lower margin of the compound eyes (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC160CDFD6DFBCD742A" box="[961,1053,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Eyes subglobose, with rounded dorsal surface and straight ventral margin (in lateral view) and elevated higher than vertex (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC167ADFC89FB2B7406" box="[1185,1275,799,826]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); lateral ocelli placed on the side of the costa frontal, medial ocellus located on the lower margin of the scutellum and as wide as lateral ocelli (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC1623CFCF1FE5774BE" box="[304,391,871,898]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Antennae elongated and filiform, more than 2.5 times longer than the fore-femur, with 13-14 segments; vertex little wider than one of the eyes in dorsal and frontal views, truncate anteriorly; median carinae present and short. Facial outline sub-vertical, rounded between the connection of the facial carinae and the frontal carinae. Fastigium of the vertex not produced in lateral view; fastigio-fascial angle rounded (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC167AFFC45FB2D74D2" box="[1187,1277,979,1006]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); frontal costa mid-length and connected with the facial carinae and reaching near the middle of the face; palpi whitish, with first three segments cylindrical and last two rounded and flattened (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC16063FB8DFC1B730A" box="[879,971,1051,1078]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC160EDFB8DFBB47309" bold="true" box="[993,1124,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Pronotum:</emphasis>
Slender, surpassing the tip of hind femora and abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC162FFFBA9FD9E7366" box="[499,590,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Pronotal disc almost flat, with an undulation at the level of the prozone, widened between the humeral angles; anteriorly straight, posterior apex pointed (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC1674EFBF5FB4F7342" box="[1090,1183,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Humeral angles and lateral shoulder carinae rounded; lateral lobe subrounded below, notoriously prolongated latero-ventrally; infrascapular area very slim and short; lateral area moderately widened (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC16086FB3DFC3473FA" box="[906,996,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Post humeral spot present or not (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC16663FB3DFF6A73D5" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC163C9FB46FF0573D6" box="[197,213,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@11.[188,1398,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. Color variation A. Color form 2. B. Form 3. C. Form 4. D. Form 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785352/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">7</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC163E6FB59FEED73D5" bold="true" box="[234,317,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Wings.</emphasis>
Tegmina ovoid, wings well developed reaching to apex of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC16740FB59FB7573D6" box="[1100,1189,1231,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC167B5FB59FB2873D5" bold="true" box="[1209,1272,1231,1257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Legs.</emphasis>
Fore and midfemora compressed, carinated with undulations, most conspicuous on ventral margin (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC16768FB65FB2E7232" box="[1124,1278,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6D, E, F</figureCitation>
); hind femora with ante-genicular tooth little developed; hind tibia ampliated from the base to the apex; the first article of the tarsi of the hind leg, subequal to the second and third articles united. 
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC1606BFAADFBEF7269" bold="true" box="[871,1087,1339,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Terminalia: Male.</emphasis>
Penultimate male sternite with posterior margin straight (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC162CCFAC9FDCC7246" box="[448,540,1375,1402]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate slender, triangular-shaped in ventral view and divided at the apex (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC163D0FA15FEE772A2" box="[220,311,1411,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
); cerci small and conical (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC1616CFA15FD6B72A2" box="[608,699,1411,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC161C3FA15FCFE72A1" bold="true" box="[719,814,1411,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Female.</emphasis>
Ovipositor normal, with the apex of dorsal and ventral valves sharped (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC16240FA31FE3672FE" box="[332,486,1447,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Figs. 6I and J</figureCitation>
); subgenital plate emarginated along ventro-apical edge (
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC16765FA31FB6872FE" box="[1129,1208,1447,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[173,1412,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Danielatettix caudatus n. comb. A. Habitus lateral and B. Dorsal view. C. Frons. D. Fore-leg. E–F. Mid-leg variation. G. Male subgenital plate. H. Male terminalia in lateral view. I. Female terminalia in ventral and J. lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785348/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Fig. 6I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3466526FF86FFC163CBFA5DFA8A72D9" box="[199,1370,1483,1510]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BE336ADFF86FFC163CBFA5DFA8A72D9" blockId="8.[151,1437,691,2014]" box="[199,1370,1483,1510]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC163CBFA5DFEB472D9" bold="true" box="[199,356,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<typeStatus id="54E7880FFF86FFC163CBFA5DFED272D9" box="[199,258,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC16260FA5DFCFD72DA" authority="(Saussure, 1861)" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[364,813,1483,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Danielatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC16260FA5DFDBA72D9" box="[364,618,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Danielatettix caudatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD4B5CFF86FFC16175FA5DFCF572DA" author="Saussure, H." box="[633,805,1483,1510]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" pagination="397 - 402" refId="ref6730" refString="Saussure, H. (1861) Orthoptera nova americana (Diagnoses praeliminares). II. Revue et Magasin de Zoologie Pure et Appliquee, 2 (13), 397 - 402." type="journal article" year="1861">Saussure, 1861</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC16038FA5DFC4A72D9" bold="true" box="[820,922,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B57C4FF86FFC16038FA5DFC4A72D9" box="[820,922,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by monotypy and original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3466526FF86FFC163CBFA79FAD17111" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE336ADFF86FFC163CBFA79FAD17111" blockId="8.[151,1437,691,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC163CBFA79FE9E7135" bold="true" box="[199,334,1519,1545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Etymology.</emphasis>
Dedicated to Daniela Santos Martins Silva, in recognition of her contributions to the American pygmy grasshoppers, as well as her friendship and unconditional support for the first author (OJCC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3466526FF86FFC163CBF9A1FAE07149" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE336ADFF86FFC163CBF9A1FAE07149" blockId="8.[151,1437,691,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC163CBF9A1FEB1716D" bold="true" box="[199,353,1591,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Distribution.</emphasis>
The only species of this new genus has several records in northern South America, and from the Amazon with a distributional gap to the south, with records in 
<collectingCountry id="F34B763DFF86FFC16059F9CAFC6D714A" box="[853,957,1628,1654]" name="Paraguay" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry id="F34B763DFF86FFC16754F9CDFB177149" box="[1112,1223,1627,1653]" name="Argentina" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13672A28FF86FFC167DAF9CDFACF7149" box="[1238,1311,1627,1653]" captionStart="MAP 1" captionStartId="9.[151,207,1171,1195]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,381,1147]" captionTargetId="figure-127@9.[170,1417,381,1147]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="MAP 1. Distributional map of Micronotus and Danielatettix n. gen. species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5786264" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5786264/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Map 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3466526FF86FFC063CBF9E9FAB27659" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="138" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE336ADFF86FFC163CBF9E9FC4A7015" blockId="8.[151,1437,691,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC163CBF9E9FEB271A5" bold="true" box="[199,354,1663,1689]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Comparison.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC16264F9E9FE2A71A5" authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez, 2021" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez" authorityYear="2021" box="[360,506,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Danielatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC16264F9E9FE2A71A5" box="[360,506,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Danielatettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC162F3F9E9FD9C71A5" bold="true" box="[511,588,1663,1689]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B57C4FF86FFC162F3F9E9FD9C71A5" box="[511,588,1663,1689]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC161ECF9E9FCB971A5" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1906" box="[736,873,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Stenodorsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC161ECF9E9FCB971A5" box="[736,873,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Stenodorsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species of both genera are slender and small in size compared to the other genera of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC161DAF935FC9A7181" authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1838" box="[726,842,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tetriginae">Tetriginae</taxonomicName>
, which are reported for America. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC167C8F935FA9D7181" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1906" box="[1220,1357,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Stenodorsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC167C8F935FA9D7181" box="[1220,1357,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Stenodorsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new genus because the body is somewhat rugose, pronotum very prolongated, pronotal disc flattened; frontal costa narrowly sulcate, almost imperceptibly widening forward to the median ocellus; mid-femur slender and not carinated; first and third articles of hind tarsi equal in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336ADFF86FFC163CBF8A5FAB770E1" blockId="8.[151,1437,691,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
The new genus differs from the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC16125F8A2FD497071" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[553,665,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Paratettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC16125F8A2FD497071" box="[553,665,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Paratettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC161C1F8A2FCDD7071" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[717,781,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC161C1F8A2FCDD7071" box="[717,781,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Tetrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genera, the thorax does not widen markedly in dorsal view at the level of the pro- and mesothorax; the hind femur is slender, not thickened, the antennae originate in the middle of the lower edge of the antennal sockets; the other two genera in comparison, the antennas originate lower than the level of the eye sockets. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC162A9F809FDE77085" authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez, 2021" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez" authorityYear="2021" box="[421,567,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Danielatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC162A9F809FDE77085" box="[421,567,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Danielatettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC16132F809FD5B7085" bold="true" box="[574,651,1951,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B57C4FF86FFC16132F809FD5B7085" box="[574,651,1951,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has the male subgenital plate apex triangular-shaped, to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC167F2F836FABE7085" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[1278,1390,1952,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Paratettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC167F2F836FABE7085" box="[1278,1390,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Paratettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC1639BF852FF0770E1" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[151,215,1988,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC1639BF852FF0770E1" box="[151,215,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Tetrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it tends to be rounded. The fastigium is not prolonged in the new genus, as is common in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF86FFC167C4F852FAB770E1" box="[1224,1383,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF86FFC167C4F852FAD870E1" box="[1224,1288,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="137">Tetrix</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336ADFF87FFC063CBFF01FAB27659" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF87FFC063CBFF01FE89778D" authority="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez, 2021" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez" authorityYear="2021" box="[199,345,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Danielatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC063CBFF01FE89778D" box="[199,345,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">Danielatettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC06269FF01FE69778D" bold="true" box="[357,441,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B57C4FF87FFC06269FF01FE69778D" box="[357,441,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF87FFC0616FFF01FD33778C" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1902" box="[611,739,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Micronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC0616FFF01FD33778C" box="[611,739,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">Micronotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the only known species 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF87FFC06795FF01FAF5778D" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Gonzalez &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Rodríguez" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[1177,1317,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Danielatettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC06795FF01FAF5778D" box="[1177,1317,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">D. caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC0663DFF01FA4C778D" bold="true" box="[1329,1436,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21B57C4FF87FFC0663DFF01FA4C778D" box="[1329,1436,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
throughout its distributional range, and in the literature records, it does not have brachypronotal forms, on the contrary, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF87FFC0620AFF49FE3377C5" box="[262,483,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Micronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC0620AFF49FE5677C4" box="[262,390,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">Micronotus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are all brachypronotal, without any record of any macropronotal specimen. The fastigium of the new genus does not extend; in addition, the frontal costa is parallel, it is not noticeably divergent, as it happens to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF87FFC06274FEB1FD88767D" box="[376,600,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Micronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC06274FEB1FE28767C" box="[376,504,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">Micronotus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
The tegmina of the new genus are ovoid, in contrast to the tegmina of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D2EFF87FFC0639BFEDDFEBF7659" box="[151,367,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Micronotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B928EABFFF87FFC0639BFEDDFEC77658" box="[151,279,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="138">Micronotus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
that are lanceolate, less widened, and less elongated than the other genera compared here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
